    "minides": "Ferrari's first-ever SUV — a 725 HP naturally aspirated V12 in a 4-door body. No hybrid. No turbo. Pure blood.",
    "description": "The Ferrari Purosangue (Tipo F175) launched in India on 29 February 2024 at ₹10.5 crore ex-showroom — making it the world's most powerful production SUV at the time of launch. Unlike every rival super SUV, it uses a 6.5L naturally aspirated V12 (no turbo, no hybrid), mounted front-mid for perfect weight distribution. Power goes to a 4WD system via a PTU (Power Transfer Unit) that keeps it rear-biased in normal driving and distributes to the front axle only when needed. Rear-hinged coach doors give access to the rear, and all four seats are individual bucket-style. Ferrari includes Ferrari shields, upgraded wheels, painted calipers, contrast stitching, and dual-axle suspension lift as standard for India. Extensive customisation via Ferrari's Tailor Made programme is available."
  },
